{"TopicId":156637,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Vitae Lunar Sculpture Project.","CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T15:27:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T15:27:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnsurprisingly, I could not find the \u0022Art \u0026amp; Spaceflight\u0022 section of these forums, so I\u0027ll try here. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrench artist Anilore Banon is planning to send \u003Ca href=\u0022http://vitaeproject.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea sculpture to the surface of the Moon\u003C/a\u003E. Banon, who is best known for her \u0022\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.anilorebanon.net/sculptures/les-braves/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELes\u003C/abbr\u003E Braves\u003C/a\u003E\u0022 War memorial on Omaha Beach, has been working on this project for the past three years. The feasibility study was performed in cooperation with Dassault Systemes. A prototype of the sculpture is to be launched to the International Space Station\u00A0today on board the CRS-10 Dragon capsule, where it will be experimentally deployed to test the behaviour of the shape-memory titanium-nickel alloys in microgravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe final version of the sculpture will be designed to fit inside a 12x12 cm space and deploy into the shape of a flower once exposed to sunlight on the Moon\u0027s surface, revealing the handprints of a million people. Fully deployed, it should measure \u0022between 1.5 and 4.5 metres\u0022 depending on the mass-budget, according to the artist. Mass will be about 1.5 kg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/IUt010RLwZw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sculpture will also be fitted with a laser that will be visible from Earth, to be used \u0022on special occasions\u0022. Banon claims that the project requires \u0022another 2.5 to 3 million dollars\u0022 to be feasible, to be financed by donations and crowd-funding.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the French band\u00A0Gojira was nominated for two Grammy Awards, so anything is possible, I suppose... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny idea how much 1.5 kg to lunar surface costs, assuming Falcon 9, say?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T15:57:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Cradle of Kraken\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:12:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShouldn\u0027t we put more people there, before we start plonking art pieces in the regolith? A permanent base\u00A0 or something?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:16:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487434355\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShouldn\u0027t we put more people there, before we start plonking art pieces in the regolith? A permanent base\u00A0 or something?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s one got to do with the other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:18:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nET will see those handprints and think that there were thousands of terrans who touched this thing, and that we can walk in vacuum without spacesuits. So, Moon\u0027s ours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the Moon will have it\u0027s own KSP-style anomaly to watch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:46:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487434355\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShouldn\u0027t we put more people there, before we start plonking art pieces in the regolith? A permanent base\u00A0 or something?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPart of the problem is that people don\u0027t have the ability to fold into a 12x12 cm cargo bay, and they weigh a bit more than 1.5 kg. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:50:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487436416\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UnusualAttitude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, UnusualAttitude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPart of the problem is that people don\u0027t have the ability to fold into a 12x12 cm cargo bay, and they weigh a bit more than 1.5 kg. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think his point was we should invest more money into human spaceflight to the moon then sending art pieces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:53:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487436620\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ninvest more money into human spaceflight to the moon then sending art pieces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not? There already are tokens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022800px-Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_2013.JPG/800px-Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_2013.JPG\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:55:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487436620\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think his point was we should invest more money into human spaceflight to the moon then sending art pieces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I\u0027m just kidding and I quite agree. But if Banon actually manages to scrape together the budget to do this through sponsorships, donations and crowd funding, then\u00A0props to her. 3 million sounds like a lot for a kickstarter project though....\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T16:59:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the video, it just looks like the mission is\u00A0supposed to be just for the art thing. If there was also some sort of actual \u00A0mission part \u00A0(eg. rover)\u00A0of it, I would actually kind of support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T17:08:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487434717\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nET will see those handprints and think that there were thousands of terrans who touched this thing, and that we can walk in vacuum without spacesuits. So, Moon\u0027s ours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the Moon will have it\u0027s own KSP-style anomaly to watch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ETs will use those handprints to find and identify those humans on Earth... then take them up into space and expose them to vacuum, to do tests. lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487436820\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not? There already are tokens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022800px-Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_2013.JPG/800px-Kansas_Cosmosphere_Luna_2_Pennant_2013.JPG\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Russian soccer team has been to the Moon?!?!??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T17:17:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959619\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487437177\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the video, it just looks like the mission is\u00A0supposed to be just for the art thing. If there was also some sort of actual \u00A0mission part \u00A0(eg. rover)\u00A0of it, I would actually kind of support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that the video is just a generic presentation (I don\u0027t even know if that is a real launcher).\u00A0Apparently they are looking to hitch a ride with one of the Google Lunar X-Prize entrants. I found another article with more info \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/one-giant-leap-for-art-the-sculpture-thats-headed-to-the-moon/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elthy","CreatedById":63317,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T17:48:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat laser has to be an impresive piece of technology...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T17:51:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487440133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263317\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elthy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Elthy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat laser has to be an impresive piece of technology...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith a large telescope meant for using lasers to measure the distance from the moon with the Apollo retro reflector, that\u0027s not a huge laser. To be seen with the unaided eye though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T18:09:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487434355\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShouldn\u0027t we put more people there, before we start plonking art pieces in the regolith? A permanent base\u00A0 or something?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs long as it\u0027s privately funded, and if sounds like it is, they can put whatever they want up there as far as I\u0027m concerned. That, in itself, would still be an achievement toward lunar mastery.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487437683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Russian soccer team has been to the Moon?!?!??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 This was on one of the Soviet moon\u00A0\u003Cs\u003Elanders\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0impactors. That sphere burst just before impact, spreading those chits all over the surface. In theory.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T18:09:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487437683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Russian soccer team has been to the Moon?!?!??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLuna-2 delivered this set to the Moon. Gather 10 and gain a bonus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487440293\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487440133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263317\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elthy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Elthy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat laser has to be an impresive piece of technology...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith a large telescope\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlus one laser impulse - minus one astronomer\u0027s eye. Laser beam, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-18T18:14:44Z\u0022 title=\u002202/18/2017 06:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UnusualAttitude","CreatedById":129962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T19:34:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487440133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263317\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elthy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Elthy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat laser has to be an impresive piece of technology...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAccording to the second article I linked it is \u0022a 10 watt laser that will pulse a couple of times each night and be visible with a pair of binoculars.\u0022 I assume such a beam wouldn\u0027t be visible from the entire globe ?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T19:46:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959785\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487446441\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UnusualAttitude\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, UnusualAttitude said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume such a beam wouldn\u0027t be visible from the entire globe ?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpotSize = 1.22 * WaveLength * Distance / MirrorDiameter ~= 1.22 * 600*10\u003Csup\u003E-9\u003C/sup\u003E * 384.4*10\u003Csup\u003E6\u003C/sup\u003E / 0.1 ~= 3 km (if mirror ~ 10cm)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T20:12:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan anyone tell what the laser will be powered by? \u00A0There didn\u0027t seem to be any solar panels on it in the video, and using an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E seems silly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-18T20:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487437683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Russian soccer team has been to the Moon?!?!??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s where they do their high altitude training.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I don\u0027t support this. To me it looks like a personal thing an in no way beneficial to the society. I believe it would fall under \u0022Fund my life\u0022 category on Kickstarter (is that still a thing?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThumb\u00A0down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T01:32:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959826\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487449540\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I don\u0027t support this. To me it looks like a personal thing an in no way beneficial to the society. I believe it would fall under \u0022Fund my life\u0022 category on Kickstarter (is that still a thing?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThumb\u00A0down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s pretty much what art is (unless directly sold to a buyer). \u00A0I\u0027m also more than skeptical of the \u0022illuminate on special occasions\u0022. \u00A0It would either have low-lifetime onboard lighting or require laser illumination from Earth (or somebody standing on the Moon with a flashlight), so I expect that is just kickstarter propaganda.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T02:17:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222959686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487441384\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257438\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CatastrophicFailure\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, CatastrophicFailure said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was on one of the Soviet moon\u00A0\u003Cs\u003Elanders\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0impactors. That sphere burst just before impact, spreading those chits all over the surface. In theory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can picture that, in the future, someone collecting those chits will have them up for auction on EBay... \u003Cem\u003Eand make a small fortune\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Moon \u003Cu\u003Edoes not need \u0022art\u0022\u003C/u\u003E. Tell Anilore Banon \u0022No, thank you.\u0022, and to stick with war memorials. When we have our first battle on the Moon (or over the Moon), then we can contact her and contract her for a memorial.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T04:41:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222960108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487470677\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111598\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordFerret\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, LordFerret said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Moon \u003Cu\u003Edoes not need \u0022art\u0022\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis tripod with a greenish Heat-Ray, which came from the Earth in a flying cylinder, and a thing with tentacles inside,\u003Cbr\u003E\nwill demonstrate our peaceful intentions and our readiness for co-operation with the selenite civilization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022heatray.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-13ufBdwqEjY/UKdr7bdKUgI/AAAAAAAANx4/5dfhc5ZmZfs/s1600/heatray.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-19T04:43:01Z\u0022 title=\u002202/19/2017 04:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 19, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JayPee","CreatedById":158043,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T05:08:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\neverywhere - and everyone - needs art\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-20T04:38:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222960241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487480928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158043\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JayPee\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, JayPee said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\neverywhere - and everyone - needs art\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile that is true, not everyone perceives individual works the same. Art to some is trash to others, and vice versa. IMO, the Moon is not a canvas nor a gallery for man\u0027s creations... and if it is, then I\u0027ve got an idea of my own. Will my idea, and others, be permitted? Who will judge me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}